{
  "id": "card_n_68a630f6f121",
  "kind": "note",
  "title": "Easton: Swine",
  "body": "(Heb. hazir), regarded as the most unclean and the most abhorred of all animals (Lev. 11:7; Isa. 65:4; 66:3, 17; Luke 15:15, 16). A herd of swine were drowned in the Sea of Galilee (Luke 8:32, 33). Spoken of figuratively in Matt. 7:6 (see Prov. 11:22). It is frequently mentioned as a wild animal, and is evidently the wild boar (Arab. khanzir), which is common among the marshes of the Jordan valley (Ps. 80:13).",
  "source": {
    "label": "Matthew Easton, Illustrated Bible Dictionary (1897)",
